            <thetext>It would be useful to be able to use the %include directive in the JFlex files to avoid repeating boilerplate code.

Currently, if we add an %include, the build fails when it&apos;s started from NetBeans. This is because NetBeans starts Ant in the current working directory, not in the project basedir, so the relative file name in the %include directive no longer points to the file to include.</thetext>
